chart.name: Inactive MTS - Trend
chart.programText:
A = data('sf.org.numInactiveTimeSeries', extrapolation='last_value').publish(label='A')
B = data('sf.org.numInactiveTimeSeries', extrapolation='last_value').timeshift('1w').publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (100*(A-B)/B).publish(label='C')

options.markdown: The chart above shows average DPM received per interval. To view maximum DPM received per interval, and access other data related to billing, go to “Organization>Billing and Usage”. Metric(s): sf.org.numDatapointsReceived Total number of [datapoints](https://docs.signalfx.com/en/latest/concepts/data-model.html#datapoints) sent to SignalFx for your organization, minus any datapoints that were not stored and processed due to limits exceeded.

For more information about the metrics used in the charts on this dashboard, see the [section on SignalFx Organization Metrics](https://docs.signalfx.com/en/latest/integrations/integrations-reference/integrations.signalfx.organization.metrics.html) in our [Integrations Guide](https://docs.signalfx.com/en/latest/integrations/index.html).  

To be alerted on problems or anomalous conditions for any of the metrics you see here, [create a detector](https://docs.signalfx.com/en/latest/detect-alert/set-up-detectors.html#create-detector-from-chart).

Data Ingest Overview
